description: {"blocks":[{"key":"7orl2","text":"This protocol details the steps necessary to quantify the concentration and size distribution of plasma-derived extracellular vesicles (EVs). This protocol utilizes a qNano Gold Tunable Resistive Pulsing Sensing (TRPS) measurement system from IZON Science. This is intended to serve as the second step in the workflow for EV quantification along with “Human Sample Processing and Isolation of Extracellular Vesicles with Size Exclusion Chromatography.”","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

These methods can also be used to help unclog a nanopore when a run is paused.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3oiv7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9eohm","text":"        Tapping → With the VPM nozzle in place, use your index finger to firmly tap the shielding cap 3-5 times. This can disrupt bubbles and assist with pore opening.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dss1l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctqpc","text":"        Clicking → Remove pressure from system and open pressure valve. Remove VPM nozzle. Raise the shielding and set it on the nanopore such that the posts of the shielding cap are resting on the arms of the nanopore. Apply downward pressure and begin to rotate until the shielding cap abruptly “clicks” downward into place.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bfkt4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"edpbd","text":"        Pressure application device (PAD) use → Remove pressure from system and open pressure valve. Remove VPM nozzle and the shielding cap. Center PAD over upper fluid cell and give 10 plunges. Repeat as necessary to unclog nanopore or reduce RMS noise.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":38}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1754c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9ldbt","text":"        Cleaning upper fluid cell → Remove pressure from system and open pressure valve. Remove VPM nozzle. Remove shielding cap and upper fluid cell. Clean upper fluid cell with filtered water and dry completely. Gently wipe top of nanopore with edge of Kimwipe. Replace upper fluid cell and shielding cap. Carefully pipette 2x ME or sample into upper fluid cell, avoiding introduction of bubbles. Proceed with run.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":26}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4agqr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"36q15","text":"        Nanopore cleaning → Remove pressure from system and open pressure valve. Remove VPM nozzle. Remove shielding cap and upper fluid cell. Clean upper fluid cell with filtered water and dry completely. Reduce stretch on nanopore to 42 mm and remove from posts. Rinse each side of nanopore with 500 μL 70% ethanol followed by 500 μL filtered water. Carefully dry each side of nanopore with edge of Kimwipe. Dry lower fluid cell with Kimwipe. Replace nanopore on the posts and rotate knob clockwise to achieve desired stretch. Pipet 75 μL 2x ME carefully into the lower fluid cell, avoiding the introduction of bubbles. Replace upper fluid cell and shielding cap. Carefully pipette 35 μL 2x ME into upper fluid cell and click “Turn On”. Monitor current and RMS noise, proceed with other troubleshooting strategies as necessary. {"blocks":[{"key":"1j10o","text":"Record 2-3 technical replicates per sample and average replicates post-hoc for more accurate concentration estimates.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fp1l6","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dkoso","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"3uevv","text":"We found that this was not typically necessary as the recordings were highly similar, however it may be helpful when troubleshooting samples.","type":"unordered-list-item"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"7v2ns","text":"Sample changeover procedures do not need to followed when recording technical replicates.","type":"unordered-list-item"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9pecp","text":"Follow “Sample changeover” procedures between samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1q521","text":"Click “Turn off” to discontinue current across the nanopore.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3s97v","text":"Remove pressure by pulling out pressure bar completely followed by opening the pressure valve.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"22cj","text":"Remove VPM nozzle and follow the sample changeover process above.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fn5e9","text":"Reduce the stretch to   by turning the knob counterclockwise.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":22,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"thickness","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error":false,"guid":"963A8EA0251E11EDA4E88B1B4FA9DC3F","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":201,"value":"42"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4dogd","text":"Rinse top fluid cell with   70% ethanol followed by   deionized water and dry completely with kimwipe.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":26,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":52,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"500","error":false,"guid":"B327CCD0251E11EDA4E88B1B4FA9DC3F","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}},"1":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"500","error":false,"guid":"B555F770251E11EDA4E88B1B4FA9DC3F","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4mnbq","text":"Remove 2x ME from bottom electrode, rinse with deionized water, and then dry with kimwipe.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cf1qm","text":"Replace top fluid cell and shielding cap.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
